Size. Reaches at least 99 cm TL (non-type NMMB–P 15684 ), but this specimen and all five other males examined ( 41–89 cm TL) were immature. The dorsal and caudal fins were well developed in NMMB–P 15684 (see
Figure 4
), so it is likely to be a medium-size wedgefish with a maximum length less than 150 cm . An investigation of size structure in the Taiwanese population is needed.
